result.name: Guangdong Barbecue Restaurant

reviews.text: Terrible service and the food is not much better. Definitely avoid
Multiple choice of meaty rice for a meal.
Way better than anything I've had in Vancouver
Still one of my old favourites. For roast meat.

Pretty crappy food with pretty crappy service. Some might call this the “authentic HK char chan teng” experience, but don’t be fooled: folks here are just rude. 
Food is extremely underwhelming. Clay pot chicken arrived with chicken unmarinated. The four treasures set meal was anything but a treasure.
The milk tea was a slight redeeming factor. Hot tip: don’t drink the free tea provided. If you’re stuck in the restaurant due to some hurricane or tornado blowing down the street, get the milk tea. If not, just walk out. 
But in short, get out of here. You can find much more fantastic food and service just across the street, like Ming’s Kitchen, or even Coral.

reviews.text: 地道中式燒味風味😋
食物唔得，黃昏5點幾，食咗义燒雞飯，啲雞唔新鮮，可能由朝賣到晚。
Great 叉燒燒肉飯，Wash it down with a cup of 凍奶茶！
垃圾燒味燒鴨當燒鵝，中餐又食物變質，收銀態度仲要差，入去食第二次都是傻仔，黑店一間，食完諗起都想嘔！欠五粒星
OK!價錢略贵
